SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION: 

The proposed financial assistance to the State of Utah for the Weatherization Managers Association will assist the
six states' Weatherization Assistance Programs by supporting and stimulating technical development activities
which improve the depth of knowledge and the caliber of technical skills of the regional Weatherization grantees
and subgrantees. The project's objectives are to facilitate technical assistance activities identified by the
Weatherization Managers Association which benefit all of the state programs in the region.


The proposed project meets the criteria of 10 CFR Part 600.7 (b)(2)(i) (B) and (D) in that the activity would be conducted
by the Weatherization Managers Association using their own resources. However, DOE support of the activity will
enhance the public benefits to be derived by increasing the amount and quality of training to be presented. The Denver
Support Office knows of no other entity which is conducting or planning to conduct any of these activities.
The Weatherization Managers Association sponsored by the State of Utah is the only region-specific organization
of which every Weatherization program is a member and, therefore, possesses exclusive capability to perform the
activities successfully.




Project Period



The initial term of the award will be for twelve (12) months, for a possible project period of three years from the initial
date of award. Possible additional funding in future years will be based on satisfactory completion of the initial
term and availability of funding.



