provides for meeting the requirements set forth 
in the regulations; 

2. The potential effectiveness of the project in 
carrying out the purposes of section 750 of 
the PHS Act and 42 CFR part 57, subparts H-I; 

3. The capability of the applicant to carry out the 
proposed project; 

4. The local, regional and national needs the project proposes to serve; 

5. The adequacy of the project's plan for placing 
graduates in health professional shortage areas; 

6. The soundness of the fiscal plan for assuring 
effective use of grant funds; 





